cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL

This paper involves the annotation of relationships between characters in literary texts, which falls under the domain of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of automatic methods for relation type prediction (cs.LG), as well as the broader computational analysis of literary character (cs.AI). The collection and analysis of annotations also involves machine learning techniques such as classification (cs.IR) and potentially deep learning (cs.DL).
